contentrichtext.text: '''St. [[Cuthbert]] of Lindisfarne''' (''c.'' 634 –687) was an Anglo-Saxon saint, bishop, monk and hermit. '''Cuthbert''' may also refer to: == People == *[[Cuthbert (given name)]] *[[Cuthbert (surname)]] ===Title=== *[[St Cuthbert Gospel]], 7th-century Latin [[gospel book]]; the earliest known Western bookbinding to survive *[[Cuthbert of Canterbury]] ([[floruit|fl.]] 736–760), Archbishop of Canterbury ==Fictional characters== *[[Saint Cuthbert (Dungeons & Dragons)|Saint Cuthbert (''Dungeons & Dragons'')]], a deity of the Dungeons and Dragons ''World of Greyhawk'' campaign == Other uses == *[[Cuthbert, Georgia]], United States *"Cuthbert", World War II Allied spy [[Virginia Hall]]'s nickname for her prosthetic leg ==See also== *[[Culbert]] {{disambiguation}}
